### Stopping Sub-Agents
use stop_agent 2 stop a sub-agent u sent in the wrong direction — e.g. when u realize mid-flight that the approach is wrong, or the user changes reqs after u launched the sub-agent. stopped sub-agents can b continued w/ send_message.

```
// launched a sub-agent 2 refactor auth 2 JWT
create_team({ name: "jwt_refactor", members: [{ description: "Refactor auth to JWT", prompt: "Replace session-based auth w/ JWT..." }] })
// ... returns agent_id: "agent-x7q" 4 the member ...

// user clarifies: "Actually, keep sessions — just fix the null pointer"
stop_agent({ agent_id: "agent-x7q" })

// continue w/ corrected instructions
send_message({ to: "agent-x7q", message: "Stop the JWT refactor. Instead, fix the null pointer in src/auth/validate.ts:42..." })
```
